Elytra (
Figs 33–36
) mutually notably ovoid, their outer margin markedly arched, length 5.70–7.00 mm, with widely arcuate humeri; anteapical angles widely arched towards apices which are in both sexes mostly almost acute with only small emargination towards distinct sutural spine; elytral surface punctate, but coloration slightly less variable and generally darker; whitish elytral maculation entirely absent.
